title: For Sale:  H&K USP 40 Custom Combat Taupe
postcontent:
H&K USP 40 Custom Combat (Taupe)RARE MODEL - READ BELOW4X 16RD MagsJet Funnel systemNovak sights with front fiber opticEnhanced inlay gripOrginal caseDocumentation (including fired case)
This is an interesting piece. So in 2004 and 2005, HK made a limited run of colored-frame USPs - Urban Grey (blueish), Forest Green, and Tan (they called it taupe). By the end of 2005, they weren't selling all that well at the time and a lot of dealers sent the colored frame USPs back to HK. HK and CDNN got together and rebranded the remaining USPs as Custom Combats - featuring a jet funnel on the 40's, Novak rear sights, Fiber Optic front sight (green on the 40's, red on the 45's), and added the Decal Grip Panels. 
There were only 500ish made of the standard 40's and 45's, of which only a few were made into Custom Combats. Ironically, there are less Tan USP40, 40CC, 45 and 45CC's than there are Tan USP Tacticals or Tan Mark 23's because of this.

title: For Sale:  Model 12 Winchester Y Series
postcontent: This is a Y Series Model 12, the re-issue of the Model 12. The original were discontinued in 63 or 64. This is the first year of the re-issue in 1972. The gun rates 95% + or - with a small spot on the muzzle that is pitted and cold blued. There are some wear nicks and freckling on the receiver but an excellent gun for 45 year old. It comes with two 30 inch barrel assemblies, one modified and one full, both Winchester factory. Both barrels and the receiver have matching numbers. Bores are bright and shinny. It is a pure trap gun with 2 &3/4 chambers and double beads on the vent rib. The wood is a fancy grade of walnut and in excellent shape. The recoil pad is Winchester. It has an Edward Recoil reducer installed. I am not sure if that is the way it came or was an add on. The reducer is $60 or so with $40 to $60 to install. Terms are payment by USPS Money order. Buyer pays actual shipping by USPS Priority Mail. This gun must go through an FFL. If the FFL of your choosing requires it be sent by an FFL then there is an addition $25 fee. There is a 3 day non firing inspection and the gun may be returned with the buyer paying return shipping if there is inaccuracy in the description. Proof of age is required with payment. Date of receipt is the day it delivered to your FFL. Make sure this gun is legal in your jurisdiction. No sales to CA & NJ.  More pictures on request.

title: For Sale:  Remington 550-1. Early production model in "very good" + original condition.
postcontent: Acquired from the individual who purchased it new, this semi auto / tube fed / .22 will chamber .22 short, long, and long rifle cartridges. The barrel year code is UU, indicating that it left the factory in 1949. This places it early in the production run, and the rifle displays with the scarce non-grooved upper receiver milling. There are no post production holes present on either the metal or the wood.The wood is in excellent original condition with a conservative estimate of 95% original finish remaining. There are a few handling marks and minor dings, but no cracks or major post production issues. The spent shell ejector shield had been removed, but the original part was presented along with the rifle for re-installation. A local gunsmith supplied a replacement (non-original ) screw with the correct thread count and length, and the shield was reinstalled.  The metal shows some carry and handling wear, along with minor spotty rust freckling and slight blue thinning  overall. The muzzle shows notable blue loss, as do carry areas on the underside and the frame. The rifle has not been tested for operation. Based on the lack of use, it will probably respond well to a thorough disassembly and cleaning (the floating chamber is noted for carbon buildup and associated issues), but will most probably not require any replacement of parts.If you are looking to add an honest and early 550-1, in well above average condition to your collection, this should be a serious consideration.Conservatively priced at $225~ or best offer. Local delivery through FFL only - no mail order.REDACTEDPS: don't bother texting - I can't receive or reply to them.
